This project has a graphify knowledge graph at graphify-out/.

- Before answering architecture or codebase questions, read graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md or use the `user-graphify` MCP tools (`god_nodes`, `query_graph`, `get_neighbors`, `shortest_path`) for structure. If GRAPH_REPORT.md says it was built from a commit other than `git rev-parse HEAD`, treat it as stale and prefer graph-backed queries against graphify-out/graph.json.
- Rebuild the graph after significant code, doc, or architecture changes by running a full extract from /home/zoe/assistant:
  `OPENAI_API_KEY=$(grep "^OPENAI_API_KEY=" .env | cut -d= -f2-) /home/zoe/.local/share/uv/tools/graphifyy/bin/graphify extract . --backend openai`
- Refresh GRAPH_REPORT.md from an existing committed graph with:
  `/home/zoe/.local/share/uv/tools/graphifyy/bin/graphify cluster-only . --no-viz`
- IMPORTANT: do NOT use `graphify update .` or `graphify hook install`; both have inflated this graph by ignoring excluded files in this repo.
- Ignore the generic `graphify update .` hint inside generated GRAPH_REPORT.md; this repo's local rule above takes precedence.
- The graph commit in git is always the authoritative clean version
